svg.title: US Map Widget
svg.desc: Represents a US map. This widget takes in an array of data elements representing state data and colors them accordingly. This widget was developed by Joe Agster for svidget.com and is licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 License.

svidget:param.name: valueLabel
svidget:param.description: The label fo the value i.e. population.

svidget:param.name: colors
svidget:param.description: An array of colors used to color states.

svidget:param.name: colorBoundaries
svidget:param.description: A series of value points to use to decide which color. The list should be one less than the number of colors specified.

svidget:param.name: defaultColor
svidget:param.description: The color to use when the state item does not fit the criteria for colorBoundaries.

svidget:param.name: labelStyle
svidget:param.description: The style object for the label. Example { fontFamily: 'Arial', fontSize: '12px' }

svidget:param.name: popupStyle
svidget:param.description: The style object for the popup. Example { backgroundColor: '#dfdfdf', fontFamily: 'Arial', fontSize: '12px' }

svidget:param.name: labelType
svidget:param.description: The label value to display. Values are 'percentage', 'value', or 'text'. Default is text.

svidget:param.name: showLabels
svidget:param.description: Whether to show the labels over the states.

svidget:param.name: showPopup
svidget:param.description: Whether to show popups when selecting states.

svidget:event.name: stateSelect
svidget:event.description: Triggered when a state is selected either by mousing over or touching (on non-mouse devices).

svidget:event.name: stateUnselect
svidget:event.description: Triggered when a state is unselected.

svidget:event.name: stateActivate
svidget:event.description: Triggered when a state is activated due to a click or touch after it was selected.
